::DarkMouse::
"Yes Commander Scorponok.  I shall investigate the cave and report back to 
you." she said grinding her teeth.
She entered the cave and looked around.  She yelled back at Scorponok, 
"Other than having room service clean up, and getting some noce drapes in 
here,  it seams to be fine."
She checked out the back caverns and the other natural chambers.  Nothing 
was found.  All the walls showed centuries old volcanic activity, but little 
else.  She returned to Scorponok.

"Sir, nothing shows up as being a problem.  This appears to have been an old 
volcanic vent at one point in time eons ago.  Nothing else.  The surrounding 
plant growth must have hidden it well enough for no one else to to have 
found it before us."
